  {
    "client_msg_id": "87765048-d7d4-47ba-8592-10a8470c1219",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "It's funny because I actually think that we're well equipped now when it comes to program introspection. Debuggers are quite powerful and we have awesome visual profilers. Where I find tools lacking is on the other side of the spectrum: the big picture. For instance, know what code is using a function/method, creating visual maps of symbols and traversing their relations. These are all super useful when working at the architectural level, but there's very little support for that. UML2.0 tried to do that, but approached it from the wrong end (model-&gt;code), while in practice the code-&gt;model is closer to how we work in practice.",
    "user": "UJPHQ8Z3N",
